{"questionId":"12346","questionHtml":"<p>A different horse breeder collected data on the time and outcome of births. The data are summarized in the following table:</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/01bc5d1a70774b876d247211b05ee4367f527584.png\"></p>\n<p>Carry out an appropriate test at the 5% significance level to decide whether there is an association between time and outcome.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\">H<sub>0</sub>: there is no association H<sub>1</sub>: there is an association &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><img src=\"__IMG__/876316b0aeed59e51f08a4aef44713fcca821c2c.png\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"{\\chi ^2} = \\frac{{{{68}^2}}}{{64.8}} + \\frac{{{{42}^2}}}{{45.2}} + \\frac{{{{103}^2}}}{{94.3}} +&nbsp; \\ldots&nbsp; + \\frac{{{6^2}}}{{10.6}} + \\frac{{{{12}^2}}}{{7.4}} - 314\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>χ</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mn>68</mn> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>64.8</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mn>42</mn> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>45.2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mn>103</mn> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>94.3</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mo>…</mo> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mn>6</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>10.6</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mn>12</mn> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>7.4</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>−</mo> <mn>314</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; = </strong>15.7</p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"v = 3{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\chi _{5{\\text{% }}}^2\\left( 3 \\right) = 7.815\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>v</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <msubsup> <mi>χ</mi> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mrow> <mtext>%&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>7.815</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">Since 15.7 &gt; 7.815 we reject H<sub>0</sub>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">H<sub>0</sub>: there is no association H<sub>1</sub>: there is an association&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">By GDC, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"p\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>p</mi> </math></span> = 0.00129&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A6 </strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">Since 0.00129 &lt; 0.05 we reject H<sub>0</sub>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1 </strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><em><strong>[8 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12346","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.29c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A different horse breeder collected data on the time and outcome of births. The data are summarized in the following table: Carry out an appropriate test at the 5% significance lev","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 8]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.12—Data collection, reliability and validity tests"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}